Class MOKnapsackParallelEvaluator

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.IEvaluator, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC, IMOEvaluator

    public class MOKnapsackParallelEvaluator
extends MOParallelEvaluator
    Parallel evaluator for the multiobjective knapsack problem. It is a generalized version of the single objective knapsack problem, where more than one knapsack can be considered. For a detailed problem definition, see:

    Paper: E. Ziztler, L. Thiele. "Multiobjective Evolutionary Algorithm: A comparative Case Study and the Strength Pareto Approach". IEEE Transactions on Evolutionary Computation, vol. 3, no. 4, pp. 257-271. 1999.

    This class requires a problem instance stored in a file with the format defined by E. Zitzler and M. Laumanns in their test problem suite: http://www.tik.ee.ethz.ch/sop/download/supplementary/testProblemSuite

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

    • Method Detail

      • configure

        public void configure(org.apache.commons.configuration.Configuration settings)

        Parameters for MOParallelEvaluator are:

        • objective (List of Objective): The list of objectives to be evaluated. Parameters for every objective are:
          • [@min] (double): Minimum value, negative infinite by default.
          • [@max] (double): Maximum value, positive infinite by default.
          • [@maximize] (boolean): Objective to be maximized (true) or minimized (false).

        A specific parameter of this problem is:

        • problem-instance (String): The path of the file containing the problem instance.
